A reception organised in Ikeja, Lagos for the visit of Nigeria's Inspector General of Police, Usman Alkali Baba was on Wednesday disrupted by thunderstorms. Baba who visited the state governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, at the State House in Marina was expected to address men of the command when a heavy rain started and dispersed guests from the venue.  A video obtained by SaharaReporters showed police officers, journalists and others scampering off to find shelter, bringing the event to an end.  WATCH: Rain, Thunderstorm Disrupt Reception Organised For IGP Usman Alkali-Baba At @PoliceNG Command In Lagos pic.twitter.com/EvAN2iYtQH  Baba had earlier been booed by Lagos residents around Oshodi-Anthony Expressway while en route to the State House in Marina. In preparation for his arrival, the state police had blocked the Oshodi-Lagos Airport Road and Maryland-Ojota axis of the highway. See Also






